{
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/calculator",
      "destination": "/index.html"
    },
    {
      "source": "/calculator/(.*)",
      "destination": "/index.html"
    },
    {
      "source": "/learn",
      "destination": "/learn/index.html"
    },
    {
      "source": "/learn/:page",
      "destination": "/learn/:page.html"
    }
  ]
}
```

This is deliberately minimal — it only rewrites the specific routes that need it. Everything else (including `/`) Vercel serves directly from the `public` folder.

---

## But there's a deeper issue to fix

The React app's build process puts its own `index.html` in the `build` folder, which conflicts with your landing page. The cleanest solution is to **move the calculator to a subfolder**.

Here's the updated structure that makes everything work cleanly:
```
veercal/
  public/
    index.html          ← landing page (served at /)
    learn/
      index.html        ← learn hub
      how-novated-leases-work.html
      ev-novated-lease-fbt-exemption.html
      true-cost-of-car-ownership.html
      dealer-finance-vs-personal-loan.html
      cash-vs-finance-opportunity-cost.html
    robots.txt
    sitemap.xml
  src/
    App.js
    index.js
  package.json
  vercel.json           ← updated version above